3. cs.LG (Machine Learning) is another likely category as the paper proposes a novel basis prediction network for predicting basis kernels and mixing coefficients. 
4. cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is a possible category as the paper uses deep learning techniques for image denoising. 
5. cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) is another possible category as the paper proposes a neural network-based approach for predicting basis kernels and mixing coefficients.
